dcterms:description: The Hodgkin-Huxley model of CA1 pyramidal neuron dynamics is a biophysiological model that captures the complex dynamics of hippocampal CA1 pyramidal neurons, including various spiking patterns in response to external stimuli.
dcterms:title: Hodgkin-Huxley model of CA1 pyramidal neuron dynamics

dcterms:creator: David Golomb
Cuiyong Yue
Yoel Yaari
dcterms:description: Synthetic data generated from the Hodgkin-Huxley model simulates the dynamics of CA1 pyramidal neurons under various stimulating currents, providing a dataset for training and validating neural network models.
dcterms:title: Synthetic data generated from the Hodgkin-Huxley model
